      "revision": {
        "keyIdeas": [
          "The difference quotient is an average rate of change over a nonzero gap h.",
          "The limit describes the value approached as h moves toward 0.",
          "For f(x) = x^2, first-principles algebra gives f'(x) = 2x.",
          "For f(x) = 3x - 5, first-principles algebra gives the constant slope f'(x) = 3."
